{
  "doc_id": "44428",
  "text": "S. aureus is difficult to induce into L-form in medium due to its thick cell wall and high internal osmotic pressure. In this study, using the method of [CITATION_1] to induce S. aureus to grow as L-form colonies, we optimized S. aureus unstable L-form-inducing conditions in the presence of penicillin in semi-solid medium. We also constructed a transposon mutant library of S. aureus and performed a preliminary screen to identify mutants defective in unstable L-form formation. We identified several genes involved in different pathways that are critical for unstable L-form formation in S. aureus. These results provide insight into mechanisms of S. aureus unstable L-form formation, understanding the emergence of antibiotic resistance, and bacterial persistence, and have implications for designing novel drugs and vaccines.",
